data.title: Galatasaray coach Terim tests positive for coronavirus
data.meta_description: Fatih Terim, the coach of Turkish soccer team Galatasaray, said on Monday he had tested positive for coronavirus and was being treated in hospital.
data.text:
Football news - Galatasaray coach Terim tests positive for coronavirus

ByReuters

Updated 23/03/2020 at 20:24 GMT

Fatih Terim, the coach of Turkish soccer team Galatasaray, said on Monday he had tested positive for coronavirus and was being treated in hospital.

Galatasaray's head coach Fatih Terim gestures

Image credit: Getty Images

"According to test results today, my coronavirus results came out positive. I am in safe hands in hospital. Do not worry," Terim wrote on his Twitter account.
